### Project Overview

A complete Procedural Content Generation system that generates realistic 3D terrain using Perlin noise, animates terrain morphing and particle flow, and introduces Biome-Aware Adaptive Noise (BAAN) as a novel research contribution.

### Milestones Completed

| Milestone | Topic | Status |

| 1 | Representation & Foundations (Perlin noise, fBm, Vec3/Mat4) | ✅ Complete |
| 2 | Space, Transformation & Camera (3D transforms, look-at, perspective) | ✅ Complete |
| 3 | Rendering & Signal Processing (Phong shading, normals, textures) | ✅ Complete |
| 4 | Efficiency & Stochastic Methods (NumPy vectorisation, LOD, Monte Carlo AO) | ✅ Complete |
| 5 | Dynamics & Animation (Time-shifted noise, particles, camera orbit) | ✅ Complete |
| 6 | Research Contribution (BAAN - Biome-Aware Adaptive Noise) | ✅ Complete |

### Key Achievements

- **53.5x speedup** using NumPy vectorisation
- **11.6% rougher terrain** with BAAN algorithm
- **3 distinct biome zones** (desert, plains, mountains)
- **Smooth 30-frame animation** with mean frame change 0.01189
- **150 physics-based particles** with Euler integration


### Technologies Used

- Python 3.x
- NumPy (vectorised operations)
- Matplotlib (visualisation)

